Copy data with HW ID _________ /________ / l input telegram l SEW l l ===============>> PLC l Drive _l / <<=============== -l__l output telegram
**********************************************************
SEW drive config:
- 8.. Unit functions l - 87 Process data assignment
_____________________ 870 Setpoint description PO1 l Control word 2 v l _____________________ 871 Setpoint description PO2 l Setpoint speed [%] v l _____________________ 872 Setpoint description PO3 l Ramp v l _____________________ 873 Actual value description PI1 l Status word 1 v l _____________________ 874 Actual value description PI2 l Output current v l _____________________ 875 Actual value description PI3 l Status word 2 v l _____________________ 876 PO data enable l Yes v l l v This changes to no when a POx paramater is changed Dot not forget to put this back to yes !
**********************************************************
"I_Ramp" is send to the drive in ms.
Speed The ramp up / down time is (Rpm) ^ / set with this parameter l _________ / l / \/ l / \ l____/ \____ l--------------------------------------------------> t (s) _
**********************************************************
"I_OFF1" & "I_OFF2"
example:
^ Speed (%) Stop signal at 5s l / 100% l______________/_ l \ \ l \ \ l \ \ l \ \ 0% l___________________\_____\___________________________> Time (s) l OFF2 OFF1 (regular start stop) 7s 10s
Ramp down time settings to be done in the drive.
OFF2 is to be used for controlled stops when there is a need to stop faster then regular, for example when there is an E-stop at a lift it is better to do a controlled stop and after that (x time in safety program) to give a STO.
Note if there is a safe stop availible on safety level this is to be used instead of the non safety signals. _
